226.680.  Prohibited areas — exceptions. — No license shall be granted for the operation of a junkyard within one thousand feet of the nearest edge of right-of-way of any highway on the interstate or primary system except the following:
  (1)  Those screened by natural objects, plantings, fences, or other appropriate means so as to render them not visible from the traveled way of the highway involved;
  (2)  Those located within areas which are zoned for industrial use under authority of law;
  (3)  Those located within industrial areas determined by the state highways and transportation commission from actual land use to be industrial or commercial areas;
  (4)  Those not visible from the right-of-way of the interstate or primary system.
(L. 1965 2d Ex. Sess. p. 905 § 4)
